# minions.yaml — Define your agent pipeline
#
# Each task runs sequentially: branch → agent builds → verify → fix → commit → merge
# Tasks are isolated — each gets a clean branch off main.
#
# The Stripe pattern: deterministic shell wraps agentic execution.
# The LLM only does what requires intelligence. Everything else is bash.

tasks:
  - name: "Fix authentication bug"
    prompt: |
      The login flow is broken — users get a 401 after OAuth redirect.
      Check the OAuth callback handler and token exchange logic.
      Fix the bug and add a test to prevent regression.

  - name: "Add rate limiting to API"
    prompt: |
      Add rate limiting to all API endpoints.
      Use a sliding window algorithm.
      Limit to 100 requests per minute per API key.
      Return 429 with Retry-After header when exceeded.
      Add tests.

  - name: "Improve error handling in worker"
    prompt: |
      The background worker crashes silently on network errors.
      Add retry logic with exponential backoff (max 3 retries).
      Log failures to the audit table.
      Add a dead letter queue for permanently failed jobs.
      Add tests.
